TY  - JOUR
AU  - Jegadeesh, Narasimhan
AU  - Kim, Woojin
T1  - Do Analysts Herd? An Analysis of Recommendations and Market Reactions
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhp093
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 23
IS  - 2
SP  - 901
EP  - 937
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article develops and implements a new test to investigate whether sell-side analysts herd around the consensus when they make stock recommendations. Our empirical results support the herding hypothesis. Stock price reactions following recommendation revisions are stronger when the new recommendation is away from the consensus than when it is closer to it, indicating that the market recognizes analysts’ tendency to herd. We find that analysts from larger brokerages, analysts following stocks with smaller dispersion across recommendations, and analysts who make less frequent revisions are more likely to herd.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhp093
ER  - 



