TY  - JOUR
AU  - Rapach, David E.
AU  - Strauss, Jack K.
AU  - Zhou, Guofu
T1  - Out-of-Sample Equity Premium Prediction: Combination Forecasts and Links to the Real Economy
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhp063
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 23
IS  - 2
SP  - 821
EP  - 862
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Welch and Goyal (2008) find that numerous economic variables with in-sample predictive ability for the equity premium fail to deliver consistent out-of-sample forecasting gains relative to the historical average. Arguing that model uncertainty and instability seriously impair the forecasting ability of individual predictive regression models, we recommend combining individual forecasts. Combining delivers statistically and economically significant out-of-sample gains relative to the historical average consistently over time. We provide two empirical explanations for the benefits of forecast combination: (i) combining forecasts incorporates information from numerous economic variables while substantially reducing forecast volatility; (ii) combination forecasts are linked to the real economy.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhp063
ER  - 



