T1  - Do Envious CEOs Cause Merger Waves?
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhp088
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 23
IS  - 2
SP  - 487
EP  - 517
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We develop a theory which shows that merger waves can arise even when the shocks that precipitated the initial mergers in the wave are idiosyncratic. The analysis predicts that the earlier acquisitions produce higher bidder returns, involve smaller targets, and result in higher compensation gains for the acquirer's top management team than the later acquisitions in the wave. We find strong empirical support for these predictions. The model also generates additional predictions, some of which remain to be tested.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhp088
ER  - 



